description._content: FILE NAME: 01_00091872 SDASM.CATALOG: 01_00091872 SDASM.TITLE: Vultee, Model 90, XA-41 SDASM.CORPORATION NAME: Vultee SDASM.DESIGNATION: XA-41 SDASM.DATE: February, 1944 SDASM.ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Originally ordered as a dive bomber, the USAAF changed the aircraft's role to ground attack before the first prototype was constructed. Designed around the Pratt and Whitney R-4360, this large plane was relatively agile but lacked speed. The USAAF cancelled the project with just this one plane completed. SDASM.TAGS: Vultee, Model 90, XA-41 PUBLIC COMMONS.SOURCE INSTITUTION: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
